g.text: UML Diagram: Class List in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.
- The arrows of the inheritance tree are

a.title: ― Position: Position of the associated member within the associated List.
a.xlink:title: ― Position: Position of the associated member within the associated List.

a.title: ― List: Simple ordered Collection defined as a list of Members where the location of each Member in the list is given by the associated Position class.
a.xlink:title: ― List: Simple ordered Collection defined as a list of Members where the location of each Member in the list is given by the associated Position class.

a.title: ― PhysicalSegmentLayout: Used as an extension point in the description of the different layout styles of data structure descriptions.
a.xlink:title: ― PhysicalSegmentLayout: Used as an extension point in the description of the different layout styles of data structure descriptions.

a.title: ― MemberRelationship: Relationship between members in a collection with directionality given by source and target.
a.xlink:title: ― MemberRelationship: Relationship between members in a collection with directionality given by source and target.

a.title: ― Map: Provides a basic pattern for a comparison map which identifies source and target members and details about their match. Source and target were retained as in describing differences and commonalities the direction of the comparison may be important.
a.xlink:title: ― Map: Provides a basic pattern for a comparison map which identifies source and target members and details about their match. Source and target were retained as in describing differences and commonalities the direction of the comparison may be important.

a.title: ― Comparison: The minimal pattern for a comparison including a mapping between members.
a.xlink:title: ― Comparison: The minimal pattern for a comparison including a mapping between members.

a.title: ― CodeList: List of codes and associated categories.
a.xlink:title: ― CodeList: List of codes and associated categories.

a.title: ― PhysicalRecordSegment: Description of each physical storage segment required to completely cover a physical record representing the logical record.
a.xlink:title: ― PhysicalRecordSegment: Description of each physical storage segment required to completely cover a physical record representing the logical record.

a.title: ― ClassificationSeries: Ensemble of one or more statistical classifications, based on the same concept, and related to each other as versions or updates.
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationSeries: Ensemble of one or more statistical classifications, based on the same concept, and related to each other as versions or updates.

a.title: ― Member: Element in a collection that can be either atomic (individual member) or composite (collection).
a.xlink:title: ― Member: Element in a collection that can be either atomic (individual member) or composite (collection).

a.title: ― PhysicalDataSet: Information needed for understanding the physical structure of data coming from a file or other source.
a.xlink:title: ― PhysicalDataSet: Information needed for understanding the physical structure of data coming from a file or other source.

a.title: ― Structure: Organized set of relationships between members in a collection. These relationships can be characterized mathematically in terms of reflexivity, symmetry and transitivity, or informally in terms of the collection's topology, e.g. network, tree, etc. In both cases it can also be defined either on all ...

a.title: ― DataStructure: Data organization based on reusable data structure components.
a.xlink:title: ― DataStructure: Data organization based on reusable data structure components.

a.title: ― Collection: Generic container that supports different types of groupings, from unordered sets to all sorts of hierarchies, nesting and ordered sets/bags.
a.xlink:title: ― Collection: Generic container that supports different types of groupings, from unordered sets to all sorts of hierarchies, nesting and ordered sets/bags.

a.title: ― ObjectName: A standard means of expressing a name for a class object. A linguistic signifier. Human understandable name (word, phrase, or mnemonic) that reflects the ISO/IEC 11179-5 naming principles.
a.xlink:title: ― ObjectName: A standard means of expressing a name for a class object. A linguistic signifier. Human understandable name (word, phrase, or mnemonic) that reflects the ISO/IEC 11179-5 naming principles.

a.title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...

Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...

a.title: ― DataStore: Collection of logical records.
a.xlink:title: ― DataStore: Collection of logical records.

a.title: ― ClassificationIndex: Ordered list of classification index entries.
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationIndex: Ordered list of classification index entries.

a.title: ― StatisticalClassification: Set of categories represented by classification items where the subset of immediate children categories for any given parent category are mutually exclusive and jointly exhaustive with respect to that parent.
a.xlink:title: ― StatisticalClassification: Set of categories represented by classification items where the subset of immediate children categories for any given parent category are mutually exclusive and jointly exhaustive with respect to that parent.

a.title: ― CategorySet: Concept system where the underlying concepts are categories.
a.xlink:title: ― CategorySet: Concept system where the underlying concepts are categories.

a.title: ― AgentListing: Listing of agents of any type who may be organized to describe relationships between agents.
a.xlink:title: ― AgentListing: Listing of agents of any type who may be organized to describe relationships between agents.
